940
01:20:42,470 --> 01:20:44,438
Aidan, please...

941
01:20:44,506 --> 01:20:46,565
Promise me you'll burn it.

942
01:21:22,310 --> 01:21:25,245
No.

943
01:21:44,766 --> 01:21:46,700
It didn't have to be this way, Lindsay.

944
01:21:46,768 --> 01:21:49,703
I thought that we were
meant to be together.

945
01:21:51,373 --> 01:21:54,501
I thought it was God's plan.

946
01:21:54,576 --> 01:21:58,239
Dylan, put the gun down.

947
01:21:59,814 --> 01:22:00,872
She's become one of them.

948
01:22:03,351 --> 01:22:06,320
She abandoned the Lord, Paul.

949
01:22:15,196 --> 01:22:18,131
What, is it your turn to kill yourself?

950
01:22:20,402 --> 01:22:21,994
Oh, I get it.

951
01:22:22,070 --> 01:22:24,561
You can't let your man's
death go unanswered.

952
01:22:26,141 --> 01:22:28,769
- Dylan?
- Would you shut up, Paul?

953
01:22:31,546 --> 01:22:34,276
Can't you see Lindsay's having
a little moment here?

954
01:22:34,349 --> 01:22:35,907
Don't do this.

955
01:22:38,019 --> 01:22:39,884
Walk away, please. Walk away.

956
01:22:41,523 --> 01:22:44,083
I don't walk away.

957
01:22:44,159 --> 01:22:45,683
Ever.

958
01:22:47,128 --> 01:22:48,720
My faith is my anchor.

959
01:23:57,766 --> 01:24:01,725
I don't know the record
for suicides in one town,

960
01:24:01,803 --> 01:24:03,930
but we gotta be climbing the charts.

